    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Camden<ptr target="nyp.00454_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1882-06-18">June 18 p m</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>Only a word to catch this evening's mail&#8212;the second letter in today's <hi
                    rend="italic">Tribune</hi> fully follows up the first&#8212;&#38; I should
                say settles the Chadwick points&#8212;Dear friend, I only wanted to say again how
                    <hi rend="italic">entirely satisfied</hi> I am with your championship, matter
                &#38; spirit&#8212;</p>
            <closer>
                <signed rend="right">Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
                <p>The "savage" letter of "<hi rend="italic">Sigma</hi>" following seems a very
                    curious one.<ptr target="nyp.00454_n2"/> I am more than half inclined to think
                    it some crafty friend who takes the mask of foe&#8212;</p>
            </postscript>
        </body>
    </text>
